==English==
===Etymology===
: The word '''virus''' is derived from the [[Latin]] <i>virus</i>, meaning roughly "poison" or "venom", and still retains this meaning.

===Noun===
'''virus''' (''pl see [[Wikipedia:Plural of virus|Plural of virus]] article'')

#A core of [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] surrounded by a [[protein]] coat that requires a living cell to [[replicate]] &mdash; often causes disease in the host organism.
#A [[computer virus]]

===Usage notes===
: ('''computer virus''') Often mistakenly used where [[malware]] would be the correct word.

